[SN]TITLE[SN]
Masked men hammer nails into man's hands in Belfast

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Police have said paramilitary involvement is a major line of inquiry into an aggravated burglary in which nails were hammered into a man's hands in north Belfast.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Masked men entered a house in Florence Walk at about 20:15 BST on Thursday and attacked a man inside.
The intruders forced him into the kitchen where they hammered a nail into each of his hands.
The victim, 23, was taken to hospital for treatment.
A woman and a baby were also in the house but were not hurt.
Police have asked for anyone who witnessed the incident to contact them on the non-emergency number 101.
